Product name: Real Leaf Wallet
Description:
WALLET
The premium quality wallet made with real tree leaves, coated in a water-resistant polymer. Leaves of Indian sal tree are used in our designs. Every leaf is dried and coloured to give the material a unique pattern. Every bump of the material can be felt on the wallet surface. No leather or toxic treatments applied. Leaves are lighter than leather, so the leaf wallets are light and sturdy too. A great gift with a great impact for the environment.
- Premium aesthetic and feel.
-Wallet's sides are backed with extra thick frame. It doesn’t bend or squeeze the cards and money, keeps it original shape. 
- Extremely tough but light.
- The coin section is an expandable pocket with a quality zinc alloy magnet.
- Wallet has softened rounded corners. Stitches are done with extreme precision.
-Available in Emerald Green, Ash Black, Turquoise, Light Brown and Orange.
SAL TREE
To produce this item, Thamon uses sustainably sourced leaves of sal tree growing in India. Sal leaves reach up to 25cm and grow on a wooden stem, thus creating stunning patterns for ethical fashion accessories. All our materials are treated without toxic components to make them resistant to water and physical damage. 15% of revenues  of Thamon go directly to the leaf harvesters in poor rural areas of South Asia.
FEATURES
-11 x 9.3 cm
-3-6 cards
-2 x Cash pockets
-Coin pouch on zinc alloy magnet
-Protective frame

Product name: Gecko/Lizard Hammock
Description:
Do you have a scaly child of your own that you love to spoil to death? Do you sometimes get teased by friends and family because lets face it; your cold blooded baby lives the life of a prince/princess? 
What better gift gift to give your reptile than a fashionable hammock for them to lounge in? 
This particular hammock is great for Crested Geckos, Gargoyle Geckos, Day Geckos, and any other arboreal gecko or lizard of the same size. If you put the hammock close enough to the ground,  your Leopard Geckos or other small terrestrial reptile would gladly climb on to it. 
These hammocks are washing machine safe, however don't put them in the dryer; They WILL SHRINK. Let them Air dry.
To help your hammock stick, put a little water on the suction cups and press onto the glass/acrylic/plastic (As in tupperware plastic) of your baby's cage. The water helps the cups stay put.
I have several designs right now, you can pick which ever you like down in the variations option! To see each design, look at the last picture posted. It'll show you all the patterns and colors we offer. 
If something is not in the variations list, its because its out of stock!

Product name: Fused Glass Tree, PDF E-Pattern, Tutorial
Description:
This pattern is for all levels! It comes with an 18 page full color instruction guide detailing each step so everyone can make this three dimensional fused glass tree. Learn to make your own slumping molds using simple materials and in three firings you'll have a tree! There is no fancy hardware or expensive molds to buy! Make it six inches or thirty six inches, the process is the same. Use colored glass or clear glass and you can even add LED lights for a festive tree. Even the lights are integrated right into the design so messy wires are hidden. This pattern is different from the "Tree For All Seasons" as it is made almost entirely out of frit and requires only basic glass cutting skills to make the trunk.The slumping techniques are also much more simple.
This version is a PDF electronic pattern that is downloaded. You save on shipping but still get all the same great features. The guide includes; a tools & supplies list, easy to follow instructions, dozens of photographs and multiple design suggestions.

Product name: Vintage umbrella with jeweled handle, 1950's umbrella with double canopy, embossed and jeweled handle and jeweled ribs
Description:
This is a very pretty umbrella from the 1950's with a 2-layer nylon canopy: the outside is grey in the center, shading to black at the scalloped edge, and the inside has an abstract print in blue and green. The silver metal handle has an embossed pattern of roses on the shaft, ending with a pyramid-shaped piece with a textured finish, set with a large faceted blue glass stone. The ribs are tipped with blue glass cabochons. The ferrule is a piece of pointed silver metal 3" long. There's a label inside reading: "MADE IN ITALY  Triminghams  BERMUDA". The piece is 34" long and 35" in diameter when opened. It's in very good condition with just a few pin holes and some faint spots. The umbrella is in good working order with ribs and stretchers intact.
